<br>
&quot; - The Plague in Qeynos -<br>
<br>
Head up [sic] by Velarte Selire, the priests <br>
in Qeynos have been busy tryin' to rid <br>
themselves of the plague in the Karanas.<br>
<br>
They have been testin' all sorts of <br>
anti-disease curin' [sic] things on animals.<br>
<br>
Some of der [sic] experiments have been <br>
halted because a thief stole some of the <br>
animals they were testin' on.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> King Kazon announced that we might <br>
be sendin' a few of our own priest </b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->[sic]<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <br>
 there to assist them with it.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->&quot;<br>
<br>
My emphasis added to the last paragraph.<br>
<br>
So you can add the Clerics of Underfoot to the list of NPC factions getting ready to fight the plague I guess.<br>
<br>
-Grimveld, 33rd Level Paladin of Underfoot <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uhalochanter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>HaloChanter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Been around a while</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/26/01 2:04:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=70.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dwarves will help fite the plague, sez Kaladim newspaper</span><hr size=1> Yeah I also read that on my newspaper round last night. Interesting, seem to be the only peeps sending help to Qeynos. Where's all the friggin help :P<br>
